In[7]:
def overlap(t1, t2):     
    return max(t1[0], t2[0]), min(t1[1], t2[1])  #  a dictionary to store the overlaps 

def overlap_t(t1, t2):
    start_point = max(t1[0],t2[0])
    end_point = min(t1[1], t2[1])
    if start_point <= end_point:
         return True
    else: 
         return False
def overprint(tup, lste):
    lst = lste.copy()
    case = []
    for ele in lst:
        if overlap_t(ele, tup):
            case.append(ele)
    lst.remove(ele)
    return case

def min_max(lst):
    start = []
    end = []
    for ele in lst:
        start.append(ele[0])
        end.append(ele[1])
    return (min(start), max(end))

big_HMM_1 = pd.DataFrame(columns=["chrom", "Pop_SEG"])
overlap_dict = {}  # Iterate over each chromosome 


#all individuals have segment

big_HMM_1 = pd.DataFrame()
one_dict = {}
for chrom in range(1, 23): #for each chromosome          
    current_overlaps = [] 
    samp_z = longest_samples[chrom] #find sample with most segments for baseline
    pg = samp_dict[chrom][samp_z]
    k = [[i] for i in pg]
    current_overlaps.extend(k)
    counte = 0
    prompte = 0 
    m = samples.copy()
    m.remove(samp_z) # find the other samples
    while counte != len(current_overlaps): #while the whole list of segments haven't been checked
        if len(current_overlaps[counte]) == 1:
            t1 = current_overlaps[counte][0]
            prompte +=1
            count = 1
            for name in m: # for name in other samples, check for overlaps in all 10 samples 
                pg2 = samp_dict[chrom][name]
                if t1[1] < pg2[0][0]:
                    break
                else:
                    if len(overprint(t1, pg2)) >= 1:
                        count +=1
                        current_overlaps[counte].extend(overprint(t1, pg2)) 
                    else:
                        break
            if count < 10:
                current_overlaps.pop(counte)
            else:
                counte +=1
    overlap_dict[chrom] = current_overlaps #dictionary to store segment overlaps that span all 10 samples per chromosome

# Preprocessing
comp = {}
genes = set()
lst = set()

def read_files(gene_file):
    """
    Read each file into its relevant dictionary
    """
    with open(gene_file, "r") as titles_fh:
        for line in titles_fh:
            t = line.strip().split("\t")
            if t and "Description" not in t:
                genes.add(t[1])

def read_gtf_file(first):
    with open(first, 'r') as f:
        for line in f:
            line = line.strip().split("\t")
            if line[4] in genes:
                lst.add(line[4])
                comp.setdefault(line[0], []).append(line[2:7])

    # Remove specific keys from the dictionary
    for key in ['chrX', 'chrY', 'chrM']:
        comp.pop(key, None)

def does_overlap(x):
    seg = x["Pop_SEG"]
    k = x["chrom"]
    count = 0
    for samp in samples:
        df = samp_dict[k][samp]
        case = overprint(seg, df)
        if len(case) >= 1:
            count +=1
    if count >= 10:
        return "True"
    else:
        return "False"


def does_overlapn(x):
    # q= x["overlaps_all"]
    # if q == "True":
    seg = x["Pop_SEG"]
    k = x["chrom"]
    counti=[]
    for samp in samples:
        df = samp_dict[k][samp]
        case = overprint(seg, df)
        if len(case) >= 1:
            counti.extend(case)
    return counti

    
def does_over_len(x):
    q= x["overlaps_all"]
    counti=0
    if q == "True":
        seg = x["Pop_SEG"]
        k = x["chrom"]
        for samp in samples:
            df = samp_dict[k][samp]
            case = overprint(seg, df)
            if len(case) >= 1:
                counti +=1
        return counti
    else:
        return "False"
    
            
def len_num(x):
    lst = []
    count = does_overlapn(x) 
    if count != "False":
        for p in count:
            lst.append(p[1] - p[0])
    return lst


def len_num2(x):
    start = int(x["Pop_SEG"][0])
    end = int(x["Pop_SEG"][1])
    return end - start  

def snps(x):
    start = int(x["Pop_SEG"][0])
    end = int(x["Pop_SEG"][1])
    chrom = x["chrom"]
    count = does_overlapn(x)
    lit = []
    for k in count: 
        for samp in samples:
            df = namp_dict[samp]
            # Filter rows based on the condition
            df_filtered = df[df["chrom"] == chrom]
            # Check if values in k[0] and k[1] are present in "start" and "end" columns
            if (df_filtered["start"].isin([k[0]]) & df_filtered["end"].isin([k[1]])).any():
                # Get the index of the first occurrence of k[0] in "start" column
                stat = df_filtered.loc[df_filtered["start"] == k[0]].index[0]
                # Get the value in the "snps" column corresponding to the index stat
                li = df_filtered.loc[stat, "snps"]

                # Append the value to the list lit
                lit.append(li)
    return lit

def variants(x):
    start = int(x["Pop_SEG"][0])
    end = int(x["Pop_SEG"][1])
    chrom = x["chrom"]
    count = does_overlapn(x)
    lit = []
    for k in count: 
        for samp in samples:
            df = namp_dict[samp]
            # Filter rows based on the condition
            df_filtered = df[df["chrom"] == chrom]
            # Check if values in k[0] and k[1] are present in "start" and "end" columns
            if (df_filtered["start"].isin([k[0]]) & df_filtered["end"].isin([k[1]])).any():
                # Get the index of the first occurrence of k[0] in "start" column
                stat = df_filtered.loc[df_filtered["start"] == k[0]].index[0]
                # Get the value in the "snps" column corresponding to the index stat
                li = df_filtered.loc[stat, "variants"]
                li = [int(x) for x in li.split(",")]
                # if chrom not in lit:
                #     lit[chrom] = li
                # else:
                #     lit[chrom].extend(li)
                lit.extend(li)
    return lit

#files
path1 = "/Users/eugeniaampofo/Downloads/CURRENT_JUPY/ELITE_CLIM/"

samples = ["CNS0254301","CNS0254302","CNS0254303","CNS0254304","CNS0254305","CNS0254306","CNS0254307","CNS0254308","CNS0254309","CNS0254310"]
big_frame_SP = pd.DataFrame(columns=["CHROM","ID", "POS","REF","ALT", "AUS1","AUS2","AUS3","AUS4","AUS5","AUS6","AUS7","AUS8","AUS9","AUS10"])
for i in set(big_HMM_1.chrom.tolist()):
    check = big_HMM_1.loc[big_HMM_1["chrom"] == i]
    position_ranges = check.Pop_SEG.tolist()
    df = pd.read_csv(path1+"elite_aus{}.txt".format(str(i)), sep='\t')
    df.columns = ["CHROM","ID", "POS","REF","ALT", "AUS1","AUS2","AUS3","AUS4","AUS5","AUS6","AUS7","AUS8","AUS9","AUS10"]
    print(i)
    print(position_ranges)
    mask = pd.concat([(df['POS'] >= start) & (df['POS'] <= end) for start, end in position_ranges], axis=1).any(axis=1) #filter for introgressed segments
    # print(filtered_df)
    filtered_df = df[mask]
    big_frame_SP = pd.concat([big_frame_SP,filtered_df], ignore_index=True)

big_frame_SP2 = pd.DataFrame(columns=["CHROM","POS","REF","ALT", "Altai","Vind","Deni","Chag"])
for i in set(big_HMM_1.chrom.tolist()):
    check = big_HMM_1.loc[big_HMM_1["chrom"] == i]
    position_ranges = check.Pop_SEG.tolist()
    df = pd.read_csv(path2+"arc_hum{}.txt".format(str(i)), sep='\t')
    df.columns = ["CHROM","POS","REF","ALT", "Altai","Vind","Deni","Chag"]
    print(i)
    print(position_ranges)
    mask = pd.concat([(df['POS'] >= start) & (df['POS'] <= end) for start, end in position_ranges], axis=1).any(axis=1)
    # print(filtered_df)
    filtered_df = df[mask]
    big_frame_SP2 = pd.concat([big_frame_SP2,filtered_df], ignore_index=True)

In[19]:
q = pd.DataFrame()
for i in set(big_HMM_1.chrom.tolist()):
    # print(i)
    check = big_HMM_1.loc[big_HMM_1["chrom"] == i]
    vals = check.vars.tolist()
    values_to_filter = sorted([i for j in vals for i in j])
    # print(values_to_filter)
    fildf = big_frame_all.loc[ big_frame_all["CHROM"] == i]
    filtered_df = fildf[fildf['POS'].isin(values_to_filter)]
    # print(filtered_df)
    # print(lolopope)
    q = pd.concat([filtered_df,q ], ignore_index=True)

q = q.sort_values(by=['CHROM', 'POS'], ascending=[True, True])
print(q)

def find_chrom(c, pos):
    "given chromosome and position, find gene/genetic material that overlaps and return"
    lst = set()
    for i in range(len(tuples)):
        if tuples[i][0] == c:
            num = int(tuples[i][1])
            den = int(tuples[i][2])
            if pos > num and pos < den:
                gene = tuples[i][3]
                lst.add(gene)
    if len(lst) == 0:
        return "No overlap"
    else:
        if len(lst) == 1:
            return list(lst)[0]
        else:
            return list(lst)



    


def find(x):
    chrom = x["CHROM"] #chromosome of row
    pos = x['POS'] #position of row
    return find_chrom(chrom, pos)


def segment(x):
    chrom = x["CHROM"]
    pos = x['POS']
    check = big_HMM_1.loc[big_HMM_1["chrom"] == chrom]
    vals = check.Pop_SEG.tolist()
    for ele in vals:
        if pos >= ele[0] and pos <= ele[1]:
            return ele
    



q["GENE"] = q.apply(find, axis= 1) #add column about genetic material
q["SEGMENT"] = q.apply(segment, axis=1)

print(q)

In[23]:
def freq(x):
    "find derived allele frequency in austrian climber samples"
    sum = 0
    for i in range(1, 11):
        if "|" in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]):
            alle = [int(i) for i in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]).split("|") if int(i)== 1]
        else:
            alle = [int(i) for i in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]).split("/") if int(i) == 1]
        sum += len(alle)
    freq = sum/20

    return freq

    

Sites_combined['samp_der_freq'] = Sites_combined.apply(freq, axis=1)
# print(Sites_combined.SEGMENT.unique().shape)

#get frequency of alleles of each archaic in the climber population
def get_match_alt(x):
    "find number of matches to altai genotypes"
    ls = 0
    k = [int(i) for i in str(x["Altai"]).split("/")]
    for i in range (1, 11):
        if "|" in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]):
            alle = [int(i) for i in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]).split("|") ]
        else:
            alle = [int(i) for i in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]).split("/") ]
        if k[0] in alle or k[1] in alle:
            ls += 1
    return float(ls)/10
   

def get_match_vind(x):
    "find number of matches to vind genotype"
    ls = 0
    k = [int(i) for i in str(x["Vind"]).split("/")]
    for i in range (1, 11):
        if "|" in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]):
            alle = [int(i) for i in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]).split("|") ]
        else:
            alle = [int(i) for i in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]).split("/") ]
        if k[0] in alle or k[1] in alle:
            ls += 1
    return float(ls)/10


def get_match_deni(x):
    "find number of matches to deni genotype"
    ls = 0
    k = [int(i) for i in str(x["Deni"]).split("/")]
    for i in range (1, 11):
        if "|" in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]):
            alle = [int(i) for i in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]).split("|") ]
        else:
            alle = [int(i) for i in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]).split("/") ]
        if k[0] in alle or k[1] in alle:
            ls += 1
    return float(ls)/10



def get_match_chag(x):
    "find number of matches to chag genotype"
    ls = 0
    k = [int(i) for i in str(x["Chag"]).split("/")]
    for i in range (1, 11):
        if "|" in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]):
            alle = [int(i) for i in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]).split("|") ]
        else:
            alle = [int(i) for i in str(x["AUS{}".format(i)]).split("/") ]
        if k[0] in alle or k[1] in alle:
            ls += 1
    return float(ls)/10

def get_match_nean(x):
    "find number of matches to chag genotype"
    s = sum([x['match_alt'], x['match_vind'],x['match_chag']])
    return s/3
    



    
Sites_combined['match_alt'] = Sites_combined.apply(get_match_alt, axis=1)
Sites_combined['match_vind'] = Sites_combined.apply(get_match_vind, axis=1)
Sites_combined['match_deni'] = Sites_combined.apply(get_match_deni, axis=1)
Sites_combined['match_chag'] = Sites_combined.apply(get_match_chag, axis=1)

Sites_combined['match_nean'] =Sites_combined.apply(get_match_nean, axis=1)

#add segment match proportions of each archaic
def seg_match(c, s):
    """Given c = chromosome, s= segment, return match proportion of neanderthal and denisovan"""
    d = Sites_comb.loc[Sites_comb['CHROM'] == c] #restrict dataframe to chromosome
    d2 = d.loc[d['SEGMENT'] == s] #restrict dataframe to segment
    # print(d2)
    # print(ereurop)
    Nmatch = sum(d2.match_nean.tolist())
    Dmatch = sum(d2.match_deni.tolist())
    denom = d2.shape[0]
    N = float(Nmatch/denom) 
    D = float(Dmatch/denom)
    return [N, D] 

def get_seg_prop_nean(x): 
    seg =  x['SEGMENT'] #segment of row
    chrom = x['CHROM'] #chromosome of row
    prop_lst = seg_match(chrom, seg) #calculate match proportions for both neanderthal and denisovan
    return prop_lst[0] #return neanderthal match proportion

def get_seg_prop_deni(x): 
    seg =  x['SEGMENT'] #segment of row
    chrom = x['CHROM'] #chromosome of row
    prop_lst = seg_match(chrom, seg) #calculate match proportions for both neanderthal and denisovan
    return prop_lst[1] #return denisovan match proportion




Sites_comb["Nean_seg_prop"] = Sites_comb.apply(get_seg_prop_nean,  axis=1) #add column with nean match proportion in segment
Sites_comb["Deni_seg_prop"] = Sites_comb.apply(get_seg_prop_deni,  axis=1) #add column with deni match proportion in segment
Sites_comb = Sites_comb.sort_values(by=["CHROM", "POS"])

# Extract Nean Deni Segment Proportions Accounting for Segments probably named the same in different chromosomes
# df = Sites_comb.copy()
Neanderthal = []
Denisovan = []
number_variants = []
genomic_length = []
gene_count = 0

chrms = df["CHROM"].unique()
for chrm in chrms:
    #print(segment)
    df_temp = df.loc[df["CHROM"] == chrm] 
    segments = df_temp["SEGMENT"].unique()
    for segment in segments:
        df_chr = df_temp.loc[df['SEGMENT'] == segment]
        number_variants.append(df_chr.shape[0])
        genomic_length.append(df_chr["POS"].max() - df_chr["POS"].min())
        Neanderthal.append(float(df_chr["Nean_seg_prop"].iloc[0]))
        Denisovan.append(float(df_chr["Deni_seg_prop"].iloc[0]))

        # Neanderthal.append(float(df_chr["Nean_seg_prop"].iloc[:1]))
        # Denisovan.append(float(df_chr["Deni_seg_prop"].iloc[:1]))
        # Check if segment overlaps with gene
        if  (df_chr['GENE'] == "No overlap").all():
            continue
        else:
            gene_count += len((df_chr['GENE'].tolist()))

In[37]:
for chrm in chrms:
    df_temp = df.loc[df["CHROM"] == chrm] 
    segments = df_temp["SEGMENT"].unique()
    
    for segment in segments:
        variants = []
        deni_geno = []
        alt_geno = []
        vind_geno = []
        chag_geno = []
        alt_all_freq = []
        index_pos = []
        genotypes = []
        
        df_chr = df_temp.loc[df['SEGMENT'] == segment]
       
        # Check if segment overlaps with gene
        if (df_chr['GENE'] == "No overlap").all():
            unique_genes = "None"
        else:
            unique_genes = df_chr['GENE'].unique()
            # unique_genes = [x for x in unique_genes if x is not None]
       

        title = "Alternate Allele Frequency \n Segment " + str(segment) + " Chromosome " + str(chrm) + \
                "\n Genes: " + str(set(unique_genes))
        
        df_chr.reset_index(inplace=True)
            
        for index, row in df_chr.iterrows():
            index_pos.append(int(index))
            variants.append(row["ID"])
            alt_geno.append(str(row["Altai"]))
            vind_geno.append(str(row["Vind"]))
            deni_geno.append(str(row["Deni"]))
            chag_geno.append(str(row["Chag"]))

            alt_all_freq.append(row["samp_der_freq"])
            #print(str(row["AUS1"]))
            genotypes.append([int(str(row["AUS1"]).split("|")[0]) + int(row["AUS1"].split("|")[1]),
                        int(str(row["AUS2"]).split("|")[0]) + int(row["AUS2"].split("|")[1]),
                        int(str(row["AUS3"]).split("|")[0]) + int(row["AUS3"].split("|")[1]),
                        int(str(row["AUS4"]).split("|")[0]) + int(row["AUS4"].split("|")[1]),
                        int(str(row["AUS5"]).split("|")[0]) + int(row["AUS5"].split("|")[1]),
                        int(str(row["AUS6"]).split("|")[0]) + int(row["AUS6"].split("|")[1]),
                        int(str(row["AUS7"]).split("|")[0]) + int(row["AUS7"].split("|")[1]),
                        int(str(row["AUS8"]).split("|")[0]) + int(row["AUS8"].split("|")[1]),
                        int(str(row["AUS9"]).split("|")[0]) + int(row["AUS9"].split("|")[1]),
                        int(str(row["AUS10"]).split("|")[0]) + int(row["AUS10"].split("|")[1]),
                        int(str(row["Altai"]).split("/")[0]) + int(row["Altai"].split("/")[1]),
                        int(str(row["Vind"]).split("/")[0]) + int(row["Vind"].split("/")[1]),
                        int(str(row["Deni"]).split("/")[0]) + int(row["Deni"].split("/")[1]),
                        int(str(row["Chag"]).split("/")[0]) + int(row["Chag"].split("/")[1])          
                             ])
#         print(index_pos)
#         #if any(x >= 0.5 for x in alt_all_freq):
#         plt.title(title)
#         plt.plot(index_pos, alt_all_freq, linewidth=2)
#         plt.xticks(index_pos)
#         plt.show()

        ## HeatMap
        #cmap= sns.cubehelix_palette(n_colors=3, start=0, rot=0.4, gamma=1.0, hue=0.8, light=0.85, dark=0.15, reverse=False, as_cmap=False)
        flatui = ["white", "darkgrey", "black"]#"#C79FEF"] ##34495e
        #sns.palplot(sns.color_palette(flatui))
        cmap= sns.cubehelix_palette(n_colors=3, start=.5, rot=-.75, gamma=1.0, hue=0.8, light=0.85, dark=0.15, reverse=False, as_cmap=False)
        variants_list = df_chr["ID"].tolist()
        snps = variants_list
        genos = np.array(genotypes).T

        samples = ["AUS1", "AUS2", "AUS3", "AUS4", "AUS5", "AUS6", "AUS7", "AUS8", "AUS9", \
                  "AUS10", "Altai","Vind", "Deni", "Chag"]
    
        if len(variants_list) > 25:
            plt.figure(figsize=(26, 2.5))
        else:
            plt.figure(figsize=(16, 2.5))
        
        plt.title(title)
        print(title)

        xlabels = [str(x) + ' | ' + str(y) for x,y in zip(variants_list, df_chr['GENE'].tolist())]
        #locations = np.arange(1, len(df_chr['GENE'].tolist())+1)
        #
        sns.heatmap(genos, cmap=flatui, annot=False, yticklabels=samples, xticklabels=xlabels, \
                    cbar_kws={'shrink': 0.6, 'label': 'Genotypes'})
        plt.show()
